NLQorg: What are the names and locations of schools in County 50 Marshall?
NLQparap: What are the school names and locations for institutions situated in County 50, which is known as Marshall?

NLQorg: What were the campus fees for each campus in the year 1996?

NLQorg: What are the campuses and disciplines where undergraduate enrollments exceeded 1000 in the year 2004?
NLQparap: What are the campuses and disciplines that had more than 1000 undergraduate students enrolled in the year 2004?
SQLorg: SELECT Campus, Discipline, Undergraduate FROM discipline_enrollments WHERE Year = 2004 AND Undergraduate > 1000;

NLQorg: What are the names and email addresses of customers who use a credit card as their payment method?
NLQparap: What are the customer names and email addresses of individuals who have chosen to pay with a credit card?

NLQorg: What are the names of the products in the Electronics category?

NLQorg: What are the names and nationalities of the members who play the violin?
NLQparap: What are the names and nationalities of the individuals who are members of the violin section?

NLQorg: What are the dates and locations of performances where the attendance was greater than 1000?
NLQparap: What are the dates and locations of performances that had more than 1000 attendees?
SQLorg: SELECT Date, Location FROM performance WHERE Attendance > 1000;

NLQorg: What is the name and description of the document type with the code 'CV'?
NLQparap: What are the document type name and description for the document type with the code 'CV'?

NLQorg: Which female employees have the roles of Editor or Proof Reader?
NLQparap: What female employees are assigned to the roles of Editor or Proof Reader?
SQLorg: SELECT Employee_Name, Role_Name FROM Employees JOIN Roles ON Employees.Role_Code = Roles.Role_Code WHERE Gender_MFU = '1';

NLQorg: What are the names and dates of battles where the result was a Bulgarian victory?
NLQparap: What battles were won by the Bulgarian commander, and what were the dates of those battles?

NLQorg: What are the names and tonnage of ships that are of type 'Brig' and have been captured?
NLQparap: What ships of type 'Brig' that were captured have their names and tonnage recorded?
SQLorg: SELECT name, tonnage FROM ship WHERE ship_type = 'Brig' AND disposition_of_ship = 'Captured';

NLQorg: Which chip models with more than 32 MiB of RAM and no WiFi were launched in the years 2002, 2003, 2004, and 2005?
NLQparap: What are the chip models that have a RAM of over 32 MiB and do not have WiFi, and were released in the years 2002, 2003, 2004, and 2005?
SQLorg: SELECT Model_name, Launch_year FROM chip_model WHERE RAM_MiB > 32 AND WiFi = 'No';

NLQorg: What are the graphics modes and their corresponding pixel resolutions for screen modes that are of type 'Graphics' and have more than 2 hardware colours?
NLQparap: What are the graphics modes and their corresponding pixel resolutions for screen modes that are classified as 'Graphics' and have a hardware colour count exceeding two?
SQLorg: SELECT Graphics_mode, Pixels FROM screen_mode WHERE Type = 'Graphics' AND Hardware_colours > 2.0;

NLQorg: Which artist prefers the genre 'tagore'?
NLQparap: What artists have a preferred genre of 'tagore'?

NLQorg: What are the file IDs and sizes of the files in MP3 format?
NLQparap: What are the f_id and file_size values for the files where the format is MP3?

NLQorg: Which books in the "Gay M/SF" category were published in 1989, who were their authors or editors, and what were their results in the book club?
NLQparap: What books belonging to the "Gay M/SF" category were published in the year 1989, and what were the names of their authors or editors along with their respective results in the book club?

NLQorg: Which movies have a worldwide gross greater than 500, and who directed them?
NLQparap: What films have a worldwide box office revenue exceeding 500 million dollars, and who were their respective directors?

NLQorg: What are the first names, last names, and email addresses of customers from the USA?

NLQorg: What are the names and unit prices of medium-sized red products?

NLQorg: What is the state associated with the area code 201?

NLQorg: Which colleges have an enrollment of more than 10,000 students, and what states are they located in?
NLQparap: What are the states where colleges with enrollments exceeding 10,000 students are situated?

NLQparap: What players do not have a yellow card associated with their records?

NLQorg: What is the status of the order placed on February 21, 2009, at 15:26:19, and what is its order ID?

NLQorg: Which users have the role code 'DBA', and what are their login statuses?
NLQparap: What users have the role code 'DBA' and what are their current login statuses?

NLQorg: What are the names of the documents that have been accessed more than 100 times?
NLQparap: What documents have been accessed over one hundred times and what are their names?
SQLorg: SELECT document_name FROM Documents WHERE access_count > 100;

NLQorg: What are the names and locations of the circuits in Italy?
NLQparap: What are the names and locations of the circuits located in Italy?
SQLorg: SELECT name, location, country FROM circuits WHERE country = 'Italy';

NLQorg: Which drivers, born before January 1, 1990, have their forename, surname, and nationality listed?
NLQparap: What are the driver details of individuals whose birthdate is prior to January 1, 1990?
SQLorg: SELECT forename, surname, nationality FROM drivers WHERE dob < '1990-01-01';

NLQorg: Which swimmer from France has a 100-meter time of less than 57.31 seconds?
NLQparap: What are the details of each swimmer from France who completed the 100-meter event in under 57.31 seconds?
SQLorg: SELECT name, Nationality FROM swimmer WHERE meter_100 < 57.31;

NLQorg: What are the names and capacities of stadiums located in Spain?

SQLorg: SELECT name, Capacity FROM stadium WHERE Country = 'Spain';

NLQorg: Which artists over the age of 30 have the famous titles "Bergen 1996," "Transmutation," "Unholy Metal Way (re-release)," and "Antithesis of All Flesh"?
NLQparap: What artists are older than 30 years old and have the famous titles "Bergen 1996," "Transmutation," "Unholy Metal Way (re-release)," and "Antithesis of All Flesh"?

NLQorg: What are the songs that have been on top since January 1, 2023, and how many weeks have they each been on top?
